OL,3,CHow will the chancellor's Budget
OL,4,Cannouncements affect child benefit?
OL,6,FOverall, the government estimates that
OL,7,F485,000 families will gain an average
OL,8,Fof #1,260 towards the costs of raising
OL,9,Ftheir children in 2024/25 and that
OL,10,F170,000 families will be taken out of
OL,11,Fpaying the tax charge.
OL,13,FMike Ambery, retirement savings
OL,14,Fdirector at Standard Life, part of the
OL,15,FPhoenix Group, said: "The tax system
OL,16,Fis awash with cliff edges and tapers
OL,17,Fwhich not only create a great deal of
OL,18,Fcomplexity but also disadvantage
OL,19,Fcertain groups of people.
